<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Well, the old adage was to snare a centaur in SK that's blue to you and let him pepper you with arrows to work on your defense.  I assume this still works well (for role-play reasons I won't kill centaurs myself).<BR><BR>In a good group, you can almost always jump in to melee a mob that is broken and trying to run to work on your offensive skills, as long as your mana is good.  I usually warn my groups if I am going to be doing this, so they won't be too alarmed.<BR><BR>Ravenwing Darktalon<BR>The Tribunal</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=526"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Ravenwing"></a>
