<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Taeil</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Newbie</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 17, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 6</FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-07-15 22:35&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Defense is a very good skill to keep maxed as it adds directly to AC. Weapon skills, hmmm, I still miss mobs 50% or more of the time. Unfortunately is was, at least for me, very hard to raise these skills. Taking a few hits when grouped just wasn't working. So I spent a bit of time each level solo meleeing mobs. Skin, coat, str, damage shield, wolf, firefist, regen [if you have it] and chain cast healing. The Ro debuff spells might be some use too. btw your offense will go up from mobs taking damage from the DS as well as melee damage.<BR><BR>At 30 centaurs are good. Skeltons and maybe some goblins in LoIO might work too.<BR><BR>From 34 on I used the cargo clockwork in Steamfont as it hits softish for it's level (only double hits for 70, lvl 30 mob, 6 min spawn, no faction) and is a controlled environment.<BR><BR>Agility (defense) and dex (weapon) buffs/equipment do seem to help with getting more frequent skill raises.<BR><BR>Best of luck. Meleeing mobs at this level isn't for the faint of heart.<BR><BR>Taeil Nantathren, Innoruuk</FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=401"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Taeil"></a>
