<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">     If you want more than just defense raises, I recommend killing mammoths in everfrost (they are around lvl 25 or so...still plenty blue at lvl 30).  Whip out your animal fear spell (you see, there IS a use for those spells hehe), and beat em from behind (snared of course).  <BR>     If you start the battle dmg shielded and meleeing, and start fearing when you are down to under 50 percent health, it is an extremely efficient and rewarding way to fight, as well (xp is good, and their tusks sell for around 10pp each).  Just remember to use treeform to reduce downtime (has a good regen bonus to it), and throw in a creeping crud if you want them to die faster (almost never resisted, which is best).<BR><BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: SerpentMage on 2001-07-26 05:44 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=1150"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of SerpentMage"></a>
