<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Wyldra</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Apprentice</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 26, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 16</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">From: Seattle<br></FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-08-08 13:14&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Just porcupine any blue con. I can still do many low blues at 47... and at 49 the thornshield gets truly nasty, so I expect it will continue some more. I do usually throw my best DOT at it too, since it does full damage when they are standing still in melee. <BR><BR>Read the porcupining strategy if you haven't. I actually don't use a weapon at all (Paw of Oppolla & Charred Guardian Shield give nice AC instead). I usually don't even have to back off to get a heal off on myself now and then either. <BR><BR>Oh and whacking on a fleeing mob won't help your defense skill, which is more important long term than your offense. <BR><BR>Plus there's just something strangely satisfying/amusing about just standing there watching a mob thorn itself to death hehe. Root them to keep them attacking when they get to low health.<BR><BR>Also a good trick to show friends who think druids can't melee LoL <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=671"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Wyldra"></a>
